U.S. Indicted for Environmental Pollution in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- The National Reunification Institute issued a white paper Monday indicting the U.S. imperialist aggression forces
for their environmental pollution during their 60  year-long occupation of south Korea in connection with the recent disclosure of part of the environmental pollution by the U.S. forces in their military bases that has lashed the whole Korean nation into fury.
 The white paper said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are a total of 850 U.S. military bases in the world but south Korea is the only region which has offered so vast area to all branches of the three services of the U.S. forces densely deployed there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are 101 military bases of all kinds in south Korea which cover at least 73.2 million phyong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Residential areas except for land, forestry, factories and business centers there cover a little over 100 million phyong. But a vast area almost equal to those residential areas is occupied by at least 37,000 U.S. soldiers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 450,000 hectares of arable land are occupied by barracks of U.S. forces in south Korea and tens of millions of phyong by the firing ranges for the exclusive use of U.S. forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is possible to measure the area of the land usurped by the U.S. military bases but with nothing can the occupation forces compensate for the land so severely destroyed and damaged by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. forces stationed in the U.S. military base district in Ryongsan which occupies an area of 820,000 phyong in the central part of Seoul discharged without warning all sorts of contaminated oil and cancer-causing substance whose pungent odor can be smelt even in the place 1 km away from it, thus polluting 491,000 phyong out of 820,000 phyong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Camp Long in Wonju City, South Kangwon Province, U.S. airforce base in Osan City, Kyonggi Province and Camp House of the U.S. second division in Phaju City in the same province and most of the areas occupied by the U.S. military bases are seriously polluted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Anti-north war exercises conducted by the U.S. forces almost every day in south Korea cause unlimited environmental pollution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 U.S. madcap war exercises left Mt. Thaebaek range, backbone of the great Mt. Paektu range, in the state of breakdown as 2 million phyong of it have been dug out. And a big rock island in waters off Maehyang-ri, Hwasong City, Kyonggi Province was lowered 15 meters due to mock nuke dropping exercises conducted by the U.S. forces without letup.
 At least 90 U.S. fighter bombers fly into a drill ground in Maehyang-ri in a day from U.S. airforce bases in Kunsan, Osan, Suwon, Taegu and other areas for mock nuke dropping exercises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deafening noise by these planes caused 80 per cent of the inhabitants in Maehyang-ri to suffer from hearing disorder, dizziness, dyspepsia, nervousness, stillbirth and all sorts of other diseases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Inhabitants in areas around U.S. airforce base in Osan, Kyonggi Province also suffer from mental disorder, heart trouble and hallucination due to noise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the recent "negotiations" held between the U.S. and the south Korean authorities over the issue of relocation of the U.S. forces in south Korea the U.S. forces side, pretending to be generous, said that they would "return" to south Korea by 2011 28 base districts which have so far been under their control. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also said they were ready to return 780,000 phyong out of 820,000 of their base in Ryongsan, Seoul, by 2008. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They, however, requested south Korea to offer 3.49 million phyong in Phyongthaek and Osan areas instead, more than four times the land occupied by their base at present. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The issue of U.S. military bases in south Korea is an issue related to more than 37,000 U.S. troops present there but an issue related to the fate of more than 48 million south Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The nation can lead a genuine life only in the land free from outsiders, the paper said, calling on all Koreans to force the U.S. forces to withdraw from south Korea to the last man under the banner of three forms of cooperation--cooperation for national independence, cooperation for peace against war and cooperation for reunification and patriotism--and hand down a reunified land to posterity.

Seminar on National Sovereignty Held in India 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- An Indian national seminar on "National Sovereignty in the Present World" was held in New Delhi on Feb. 12 on the
occasion of the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 Present there were figures of international and regional organizations and Indian political and public figures including Vishwanath, secretary general of the "International Kim Il Sung Prize" Council and director-general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, Harish Gupta, secretary general of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea, Romesh Chandra, honorary president of the World Peace Council, former Indian Foreign Minister P. Shiv Shankar who is chairman of the All India Indo-Korean Friendship Association, Suneet Chopra, member of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of India (Marxist) and joint secretary of the All-India Agricultural Workers' Union, and Om Prakash Mantri, secretary general of the Asian Regional Committee to Support Korea's Reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vishwanath said in his report that leader Kim Jong Il set the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche started by President Kim Il Sung as his life-long task in the first days of his revolutionary activities and performed immortal feats for the Party, the revolution, the country and the people in the whole course of his revolutionary activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through his energetic ideological and theoretical activities Kim Jong Il formulated the revolutionary idea of Kim Il Sung as an integral system of idea, theory and method of Juche and strengthened and developed the Workers' Party of Korea into a revolutionary party of Juche type. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The figures who followed him on the rostrum said the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il was the only correct political mode  guaranteeing the sovereignty of each country and nation, global peace and security and people's happiness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They expressed undivided support to the statement of the DPRK Foreign Ministry dated Feb.10, saying it was a just measure taken to defend the supreme interests of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the seminar.

65th Anti-U.S. Solidarity Rally in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- The 65th anti-U.S. solidarity rally was reportedly held in the vicinity of the U.S. embassy in Seoul on February 15.
 Recalling the announcement at the "meeting of south Korea-U.S. alliance security policy initiative" that the "strategic flexibility" of the U.S. forces would be discussed in camera, the speakers said this meant the full acceptance of the demand of the United States. They called for an immediate stop to the debate on the "strategic flexibility" which runs counter to the peace and reunification of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said the remarks of U.S. Assistant Secretary of Defense Rawless that the super brigade would be deployed in south Korea, the first of such step in the world, were intended to reinforce the U.S. forces stationed in south Korea and force the introduction of U.S. weapons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Calling attention to the scheme of the Defense Ministry to make a unilateral survey for the expansion of a U.S. military base from February 21, ignoring the will of the residents of Phyongthaek, they called for a relentless fight against the expansion of the U.S. military base.

Japan's Harsh Resident General Policy Disclosed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed article discloses the harsh resident-general policy enforced by the Japanese imperialists and terms the "Jongmi Seven-Point Treaty" cooked up by them illegal and invalid.
 The article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After cooking up the "Ulsa Five-Point Treaty" in a brigandish manner, the Japanese imperialists proclaimed a "system of setting up a residency-general and local executive bodies directly under it" by what they called "imperial order" No. 267 on Dec. 20, 1905. They began enforcing the resident-general policy over Korea in real earnest from Feb.1 next year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resident-general was little short of a de facto "governor-general" empowered to control all fabrics of social and political life such as politics, economy, military and culture as a supreme ruler who exercised his authority over legislature, judicature and the executive, and the prerogative of command over the army and all other affairs in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hirobumi Ito was appointed as a resident-general at that time. He exercised unlimited real power as he had the right to rule Korea and the prerogative of command over the Japanese imperialist aggression troops stationed in it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While pursuing the resident-general policy, the Japanese imperialists desperately worked to politically subjugate Korea in reliance upon their huge aggressor forces. One of the typical examples of this was the fact that they replaced the cabinet of Pak Je Sun, who had played a dirty role in fabricating the subordinate "Ulsa Five-Point Treaty" as a pro-Japanese lackey, by the one of Ri Wan Yong, who was also pro-Japanese stooge, in May 1907 in a bid to isolate the royal palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was stipulated in the "Ulsa Five-Point Treaty" that the diplomatic right of Korea would be transferred to Japan but the former was, in fact, deprived even of the right to administer internal affairs by the force of the resident-general policy. And it was legalized according to Japan's new plan for aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "Jongmi Seven-Point Treaty" like the "Ulsa Five-Point Treaty" was an illegal document as it lacked any legal validity. All treaties and laws in force at that time had no signature of Kojong, the supreme executive in the feudal government of the Ri Dynasty, among other things. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In face of strong opposition of Emperor Kojong the "Jongmi Seven-Point Treaty" was unilaterally concluded by the Japanese imperialists. In consequence it is recorded in history as a false document lacking any legal validity as it had only the stamp of Ri Wan Yong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese imperialists enforced the harsh resident-general policy and colnial rule over Korea by the force of such illegal treaty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan should admit the crimes related to the resident-general policy and the false treaty committed by the Japanese imperialists in the past and apologize to the Korean people for the misfortune, pain and disasters they brought to them.

Press Conference and Film Show at Russian Embassy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- A press conference and a film show took place at the Russian embassy in Pyongyang on Monday on the occasion of the
"Day of Defenders of Motherland."
 Present there were media persons in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ambassador Andrei Karlov and staff members of the Russian embassy were on hand.
 Igor Pablov, military attache of the Russian embassy, in his address underlined the significance and importance of the day, saying the Soviet soldiers and people displayed unexampled bravery in the Great Patriotic War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The armed forces of Russia fully support the further development of military-political and military-technical cooperation with the DPRK on the principle of equality, mutual benefit and neighborliness, he stated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants saw the Russian feature film "Special Unit."

New Materials on Japanese Imperialists' Aggression and Looting Unearthed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kaesong, February 21 (KCNA) -- More than 20 pieces of documents and photos disclosing the Japanese imperialists' crimes in their aggression and looting in Korea were unearthed to be displayed in the Kaesong City Hall of Class Education.
 They include materials on the extensive incitement of war fever by the Japanese imperialists and their indiscreet looting of historical relics and special products including Kaesong Koryo Insam (ginseng) in the area of Kaesong during their occupation of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also included are materials on the robbery of the Japanese imperialists who pillaged King Kongmin's Mausoleum and other graves of their precious cultural relics and pictures of the 13-storeyed Marble Pagoda of the Kyongchon Temple and the stone lantern of the Hyonhwa Temple they carried away to Japan only to bring back to Seoul, forced by the strong protest and denunciation of Koreans, and the East Gate of the Inner Wall they pulled down when building the Kaesong Juvenile Prison and a press report about the looting of the gold decoration of a Buddha image. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on display are pictures of the then Insam-producing association, the building of the Insam Shrine and "a contract on the consignment of Insam" imposed by the Mitsui Zaibatsu of Japan upon the government of the Ri Dynasty, which lay bare the crimes of the Japanese imperialist aggressors in monopolizing the cultivation, processing, sale and export of the world-famous Kaesong Koryo Insam and taking away all of it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new materials on display were found out by officials of the Kaesong City Hall of Class Education while meeting with many people who experienced and witnessed the pillage and ascertaining materials.

Kim Jong Il's Birthday Celebrated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- Kong Sam Ol, deputy prime minister for the Royal Palace of Cambodia, hosted a reception on February 16 in celebration of leader Kim Jong Il's birthday.
 Present there on invitation were Ambassador Choe Han Chun and staff members of the DPRK embassy in Phnom Penh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were the chief of protocol for the king and the secretary and the under-secretary of state of the Ministry of the Royal Palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the meantime, the DPRK embassy in Ulan Bator was visited by different personages of this country on Feb. 15 to celebrate Kim Jong Il's birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Among those visitors were the chairman of the Mongolian Mt. Paektu Association, the vice-chairman of the Mongolia-Korea Friendship Society, the director of the Kim Jong Suk Kindergarten, the commander of Unit 0151 of the Frontier Forces of Mongolia and the director of "Gor King-Erdene" Institute of Teachers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They laid bouquets before the portraits of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and paid respects to them.

Koryo Medical Science Develops in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- The Academy of Koryo Medical Science of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has made signal successes which are of great clinical significance in the efforts for developing and putting on a scientific basis the traditional Koryo medicine in accordance with the requirement of the present times.
 Dr.Hyon Chol, vice-president of the academy, told KCNA that the scientists of the academy have formulated in a scientific way traditional therapies for hypertension, angina pectoris, hypertrophy, hyperlipemia, chronic pancreatitis and epilepsy with natural Koryo pharmaceuticals, acupuncture, moxibustion, cupping, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have also found out traditional medicines for protecting visceral organs after operation of gastric cancer at its early stage and traditional therapies for spontaneous gangrene, anal disease, cataract at its early stage and idiopathic hypoacusis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have expounded the theoretical foundation of the theory on the four physical characteristics of human body in a scientific way and made a computer program to classify the constitutions of human bodies. They also developed new kinds of Koryo medicines including pills made from Astragalus membranaceus. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vice-president added that they would put the already-achieved successes on a solid scientific basis and continue to deepen their research so as to make the successes pay off in clinical practice and develop the traditional medicine of the nation.

New Medicine for Anemia Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- A new kind of medicine for anemia has been developed at the Kim Man Yu Hospital in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 The tablet is made of humic acid and other matters mixed with iron. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is applicable to the patients suffering from iron-lack anemia caused by pregnancy, nursing, puberty and hemorrhage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The rate of its side-effect on digestion is 9 percent, much lower than other anemia medicines, and the treatment term 15 days shorter than them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Clinical examinations show that humic acid improves sexual function. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was appreciated at the 8th National Exhibition of Inventions and New Technologies held last year.

Kimjongilia Festival Closes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- The 9th Kimjongilia Festival that opened on Feb. 12 on the occasion of the February holiday closed at the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition today with due ceremony.
 Put on display were 19,000 potted Kimjongilias in exceptionally fuller bloom presented by armed forces organizations, ministries, national institutions, provincial units, servicepersons, working people and school youth and children. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Diplomatic missions of different countries here, missions of international organizations, the Pyongyang mission of the National Democratic Front of south Korea, scores of friendship and solidarity organizations and individual figures in different countries and overseas Koreans also presented immortal flowers to the festival carrying their sincerity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival venue was visited by senior party, state and army officials, officials of ministries and national institutions, at least 800,000 officers and men of the Korean People's Army, working people and school youth and children, a delegation of the International Liaison Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, the diplomatic corps, military attaches corps and economic and commercial councilors' corps here and members of delegations and art troupes from at least 100 countries and overseas Koreans staying in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the closing ceremony were Pak Pong Ju, Yang Hyong Sop, Jong Ha Chol, Kwak Pom Gi, Cabinet members, leading officials of ministries, national institutions and working people's organizations, officials concerned, servicepersons, working people and school youth and children. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Diplomas and cups of special prize of the immortal flower were awarded to the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, Ri Sang Ryol-led unit of the KPA, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and the Secretariat of the Cabinet which got the highest appreciation at the festival, diplomas of the best prizes of the immortal flower went to 55 units and diplomas of prizes of the same flower to 38 units. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Diplomas of the best prizes and diplomas of prizes of the immortal flower, prizes of merit and gold, silver and bronze medals were conferred upon 22 individual servicepersons, working people and school youth and children and diplomas of the best prizes of the immortal flower and gold medals went to two Chinese residents in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kang Nung Su, chairman of the DPRK Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Committee made a closing address.

Pyongyangites Vow to Bring about Great Revolutionary Surge
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- At least 100,000 Pyongyangites gathered at Kim Il Sung Square today to vow to thoroughly implement tasks set forth in the appeal to all the servicepersons and people made at the meeting for the general march for the Songun revolution.
 They called for intensifying the drive for effecting a fresh great revolutionary surge to greet the 60th anniversaries of the Workers' Party of Korea and national liberation as grand festivals of victors in the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting was attended by Pak Pong Ju, Yang Hyong Sop, Choe Thae Bok, Jong Ha Chol, Kim Jung Rin and Cabinet members, leading officials of the ministries, national institutions and working people's organizations and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ryang Man Gil, chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee, read out the appeal of the meeting for the general march for the Songun revolution to be followed by speeches of representatives of people of various strata. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hwa Suk, chairwoman of the Cooperative Farm Management Committee of Sadong District, stated that officials and working people in the field of agriculture will devotedly work to till the land of socialism, highly aware of their obligations as citizens of the DPRK, and thus fulfil their responsibility for the nation's grain production. She said that they would bring about fresh innovation in the agricultural production this significant year by thoroughly implementing the party's policy for the agricultural revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Yong Yong, manager of the Kangdong Area Coal Mining Complex, said that all the officials and coal miners of the complex would dynamically step up the general march to bring about a radical turn in the coal production this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Song Chol, first secretary of the Pyongyang City Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, said that the on-going general charge calls on the hot-blooded youngsters to perform miracles and feats. He underscored the need for young Koreans to dedicate their wisdom, sweat and enthusiasm to the charge with a high ambition and strong desire just as the young heroes did in the period of the great Chollima surge so as to leave traces of their worthwhile and noble life in the course of the general march for the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Pok Nam, chief secretary of the Mangyongdae District Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, said that the master key to victory in the general march for the Songun revolution is in the hands of officials. He called on all the officials to guide this year's general march in a responsible manner, bearing deep in mind the high expectation of the party and the requirements of the stirring times and thus fully discharge their duty as officials in the Songun era.
